abstract: The globally conscious mayor of Paris gets things done. But inviting traffic jams and proposing a nudist camp may not be the best places to start.
snippet: The globally conscious mayor of Paris gets things done. But inviting traffic jams and proposing a nudist camp may not be the best places to start.
lead_paragraph: PARIS — If you want a lively dinner party conversation in Paris these days, just mention “les voies sur berges” — the express car lanes that run along the Seine — and your guests will soon be at one another’s throats.

abstract: Advocacy groups are spending tens of millions of dollars on campaign ads arguing that stronger firearms restrictions can reduce crime.
snippet: Advocacy groups are spending tens of millions of dollars on campaign ads arguing that stronger firearms restrictions can reduce crime.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — With guns emerging as a major flash point in the presidential race and campaigns nationwide, gun-control advocates are spending tens of millions of dollars on a central message: Stronger firearms laws can reduce gun violence.

abstract: “If governments tax products like sugary drinks, they can reduce suffering and save lives,” a World Health Organization official said.
snippet: “If governments tax products like sugary drinks, they can reduce suffering and save lives,” a World Health Organization official said.
lead_paragraph: The World Health Organization on Tuesday urged countries to impose a tax on sugary drinks to battle the growing obesity epidemic and presented new data on the beneficial health effects of such a tax.

abstract: According to documents posted online by WikiLeaks, Mrs. Clinton displayed an easy comfort with business and embraced unfettered trade in paid speeches to financial firms.
snippet: According to documents posted online by WikiLeaks, Mrs. Clinton displayed an easy comfort with business and embraced unfettered trade in paid speeches to financial firms.
lead_paragraph: In lucrative paid speeches that Hillary Clinton delivered to elite financial firms but refused to disclose to the public, she displayed an easy comfort with titans of business, embraced unfettered international trade and praised a budget-balancing plan that would have required cuts to Social Security, according to documents posted online Friday by WikiLeaks.

abstract: Last week’s top events included the New York Film Festival’s opening night party, the Park Avenue Armory Gala, and the American Red Cross’s annual tribute.
snippet: Last week’s top events included the New York Film Festival’s opening night party, the Park Avenue Armory Gala, and the American Red Cross’s annual tribute.
lead_paragraph: The 54th New York Film Festival opened on Sept. 30 with the premiere of “13TH,” a documentary on racial injustice directed by Ava DuVernay; the after-party was held at the Tavern on the Green. The Park Avenue Armory honored Michael R. Bloomberg and Rob Ashford at its annual gala on Wednesday. And the American Red Cross in Greater New York honored numerous “heroes” at its gala, also Wednesday, at the American Museum of Natural History.

abstract: The construction of Sunrise Cooperative, a warehouse that is being converted into an auto mart, has stopped because the group has ran out of funds.
snippet: The construction of Sunrise Cooperative, a warehouse that is being converted into an auto mart, has stopped because the group has ran out of funds.
lead_paragraph: Mario Chasi stood in the middle of one of the 45 corrugated steel stalls that line the former warehouse in the Hunts Point section of the Bronx where he hopes to re-establish his body shop.
